  "name": "Doru",
  "pfs": {
    "availability": "Standard",
    "subtype": "pfs",
    "type": "stat_block_section"
  },
  "schema_version": 1.4,
  "sections": [
    {
      "name": "Doru",
      "sections": [
        {
          "image": {
            "image": "Sidebar_2_AdditionalLore.png",
            "name": "Additional Lore",
            "type": "image"
          },
          "name": "Doru Secrets",
          "sidebar_heading": "Additional Lore",
          "sidebar_type": "additional_lore",
          "sources": [
            {
              "link": {
                "alt": "Monster Core 2 pg. 110",
                "aonid": 276,
                "game-obj": "Sources",
                "name": "Monster Core 2 pg. 110",
                "type": "link"
              },
              "name": "Monster Core 2",
              "page": 110,
              "type": "source"
            }
          ],
          "subtype": "sidebar",
          "text": "Despite dorus' obsession, not all secrets capture their focus\u2014instead, each fixates on a unique topic. Many are interested in the history of a particular mortal ancestry, while others delve into riddles, mathematical puzzles, or even local gossip.",
          "type": "section"
        }
      ],
      "sources": [
        {
          "link": {
            "alt": "Monster Core 2 pg. 110",
            "aonid": 276,
            "game-obj": "Sources",
            "name": "Monster Core 2 pg. 110",
            "type": "link"
          },
          "name": "Monster Core 2",
          "page": 110,
          "type": "source"
        }
      ],
      "text": "These deceivers whisper fetid lies, sowing dark and dread inspiration into foolish mortal ears. Dorus serve as the spies and messengers of the divs. With silver tongues and wicked motives, they often pledge themselves to vainglorious and deluded spellcasters, whom they ply with wild conspiracies and rumors of deception among friends and foes alike; in the process, they push supposed masters to despotism and murderous revenge. All the while, dorus wean secrets and weaknesses from their marks. In the end, nearly every doru turns on their supposed liege, destroying the reputation and even causing the death of the person the doru pretended to serve.",
      "type": "section"
    }
  ],
  "sources": [
    {
      "link": {
        "alt": "Monster Core 2 pg. 110",
