      "size": "Tiny",
      "subtype": "creature_type",
      "traits": [
        {
          "classes": [
            "size"
          ],
          "edition": "legacy",
          "game-id": "bb6959f434e4e1dc9ae2c02ca9015792",
          "game-obj": "Traits",
          "name": "Tiny",
          "sources": [
            {
              "errata": {
                "alt": "2.0",
                "game-obj": "Sources",
                "name": "2.0",
                "type": "link"
              },
              "link": {
                "alt": "Core Rulebook pg. 474",
                "href": "https://paizo.com/products/btq01y0k?Pathfinder-Core-Rulebook",
                "name": "Core Rulebook pg. 474",
                "type": "link"
              },
              "name": "Core Rulebook",
              "page": 474,
              "type": "source"
            }
          ],
          "text": "*Space:* Less than 5 feet, *Reach (Tall):* 0 feet, *Reach (Long):* 0 feet.  Multiple Tiny creatures can occupy the same square.  At least four can fit in a single square, though the GM might determine that even more can fit.  Tiny creatures can occupy a space larger creature as well, and if their reach is 0 feet, they must do so in order to attack.",
          "type": "trait"
        },
        {
          "classes": [
            "monsters"
          ],
          "edition": "legacy",
          "game-id": "8b6dda4938a126caf68c10c177f6c261",
          "game-obj": "Traits",
          "name": "Div",
          "sources": [
            {
              "link": {
                "alt": "Bestiary 3 pg. 308",
                "aonid": 66,
                "game-obj": "Sources",
                "name": "Bestiary 3 pg. 308",
                "type": "link"
              },
              "name": "Bestiary 3",
              "page": 308,
              "type": "source"
            }
          ],
          "text": "Divs are a family of fiends spawned from the spirits of evil genies within the desolation of Abaddon. Most divs are neutral evil. They typically have greater darkvision and weakness to cold iron and good damage.",
          "type": "trait"
        },
        {
          "alternate_link": {
            "alternate_type": "legacy",
            "aonid": 70,
            "game-obj": "Traits",
            "type": "alternate_link"
          },
          "classes": [
            "creature_type"
          ],
          "edition": "remastered",
          "game-id": "f4bfadf0db13af1b3cde6e4663b082db",
          "game-obj": "Traits",
          "name": "Fiend",
          "sources": [
            {
              "errata": {
                "alt": "2.0",
                "aonid": 216,
                "game-obj": "Sources",
                "name": "2.0",
                "type": "link"
              },
              "link": {
                "alt": "Player Core pg. 456",
                "aonid": 216,
                "game-obj": "Sources",
                "name": "Player Core pg. 456",
                "type": "link"
              },
              "name": "Player Core",
              "page": 456,
              "type": "source"
            }
          ],
          "text": "Creatures that hail from or have a strong connection to the unholy planes are called fiends. Fiends can survive the basic environmental effects of planes in the Outer Sphere.",
          "type": "trait"
        },
        {
          "classes": [
            "monsters"
          ],
          "edition": "remastered",
          "game-id": "6309897c89780f17449b984cbb6d26cb",
          "game-obj": "Traits",
          "links": [
            {
              "alt": "holy",
              "aonid": 517,
              "game-obj": "Traits",
              "name": "holy",
              "type": "link"
            }
          ],
          "name": "Unholy",
          "sources": [
            {
              "errata": {
                "alt": "2.0",
                "aonid": 216,
                "game-obj": "Sources",
                "name": "2.0",
                "type": "link"
              },
              "link": {
                "alt": "Player Core pg. 462",
                "aonid": 216,
                "game-obj": "Sources",
                "name": "Player Core pg. 462",
                "type": "link"
              },
              "name": "Player Core",
              "page": 462,
              "type": "source"
            }
          ],
          "text": "Effects with the unholy trait are tied to powerful magical forces of cruelty and sin. They often have stronger effects on holy creatures. Creatures with this trait are strongly devoted to unholy causes, and often have weakness to holy. If a creature with weakness to unholy uses an unholy item or effect, it takes damage from its weakness.",
          "type": "trait"
        }
      ],
      "type": "stat_block_section"
    },
